💡 A Quick Reality Check on Dependency Bloat
While removing debug from devDependencies resolves the structural file conflict, running npm install on this project is going to be incredibly unstable.

This file is bloated with over 700 packages and fundamentally competing tools. It has multiple frontend frameworks (React, Vue), competing backend architectures (Express, Koa, Fastify, NestJS, Next.js, Remix, Hapi), multiple database ORMs, competing test runners, and heavily overlapping utilities. Installing this will almost certainly trigger a flood of ERESOLVE (peer dependency) errors in modern versions of npm because many of these specific versions don't play well together.

If this is meant to be a real, workable app, I highly recommend completely wiping out the dependencies block and installing only the tools you actually need!

